# Code guide: C#

---

## Overview

**Guide quality: 3/5** — One authoritative source (Google C#) merged; consensus and per-source rules derived from it. Trustworthiness high for that source; completeness will improve when Microsoft/Goat/others are merged. Re-score after adding sources or resolving conflicts.

C# is a strongly typed, object-oriented language on the .NET runtime with modern features (generics, async, pattern matching). **Best for:** backend services, desktop and mobile apps (Xamarin/MAUI), Unity, tooling, and Windows ecosystem development. **Avoid for:** low-level systems programming (prefer C++/Rust), unmanaged interop-heavy code. **Ecosystem:** .NET SDK, NuGet, MSBuild; [official docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/csharp/).

